gov.nih.nlm.meme.client
Class MaintenanceClient

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.client.ClientAPI
      gov.nih.nlm.meme.client.MaintenanceClient
public class MaintenanceClient
extends ClientAPI

This client API is used to preform MID Maintenance operations. See ClientAPI for information on configuring properties required by this class. With the properties properly configured, accessing maintenance data services is as simple as instantiating class and calling its methods. For example, 

   // Instantiate client
   // connected to default data source ("editing-db")
   MaintenanceClient client = new MaintenanceClient();

   // Assign cuis
   client.assignCuis();

executeQuery


public void executeQuery(String query,
                         String inverse_query)
                  throws MEMEException




Executes the specified query and logs the operation (SERVER CALL).
 This method can be used to arbitrarily change the database in a logged
 way that can be synched with MRD. This method supports the ability to
 undo the query later with an inverse query.





Parameters:
query - the query to execute
inverse_query - the query to execute to undo the first query

Throws:

MEMEException - if anything goes wrong










loadTable


public void loadTable(String table)
               throws MEMEException




Requests that the server log the contents of a table as a "load table action"
 (SERVER CALL).
 This is a way of logging the loading of an ad-hoc table.  The table should
 be created and populated, and then this method should be called. It will
 guarantee that actions logging the creation/loading of the table will be
 added to the system to allow them to by synched to MRD.





Parameters:
table - the table whose loading should be logged

Throws:

MEMEException - if anything goes wrong










exec


public void exec(String[] command,
                 String[] env)
          throws MEMEException




Executes the specified command with the specified environment and
 logs the call (SERVER CALL).  Allows a generic script call
 to be made, logged, and synched with MRD.





Parameters:
command - the command
env - the environment (e.g. { "MEME_HOME=/d5/MEME4","ORACLE+HOME=x"}

Throws:

MEMEException - if anything goes wrong










exec


public void exec(String[] command,
                 String[] inverse_command,
                 String[] env)
          throws MEMEException




Executes the specified command with the specified environment and
 logs the call and the ability to undo(SERVER CALL).
 Allows a generic script call to be made, logged, and synched with MRD.
 The inverse command allows this action to be undone by inovking that
 inverse command.





Parameters:
command - the command
inverse_command - the command that undoes the first command
env - the environment (e.g. { "MEME_HOME=/d5/MEME4","ORACLE+HOME=x"}

Throws:

MEMEException - if anything goes wrong
